> so do you really think C++ (and OOP in general) is a 
> retrogression compared to C ??
Please don't confuse object oriented with C++. Decent programmers can write
object oriented assembler, fortran or even cobol (although they normally leave
in the latter case). Linux is heavily object oriented but without using a 
glorified pre-processor on it
